article.description: Brandon Kamga scored 21 points -- 11 at the foul line -- and Cal State Fullerton held off UC Davis 78-74 on Wednesday.
article.headline: Kamga's late free throws helps CS Fullerton over UC Davis
article.linkText: Kamga's late free throws helps CS Fullerton over UC Davis
article.story: DAVIS, Calif. -- Brandon Kamga scored 21 points -- 11 at the foul line -- and Cal State Fullerton held off UC Davis 78-74 on Wednesday. Wayne Arnold scored 14 off the bench with four 3-pointers, Davon Clare 12 and Austen Awosika and Vincent Lee 11 apiece. Arnold's 3-pointer with 10:35 before halftime broke an 11-all tie and the Titans (7-13, 2/3 Big West) never trailed again. Awosika's layup with 12:11 left Cal State Fullerton a 49-39 lead before the Aggies (8-12, 2-2) went on a 13-3 run to tie it at 52 with six minutes left. Arnold responded with a 3 to end the threat and the Titans held on going 12 of 14 from the foul line in the final 79 seconds. Kamga finished 11 of 12 from the line overall and 9 of 10 in the final 1:19. Ezra Manjon led the Aggies with 24 points and Elijah Pepper and Damion Squire each scored 10. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25
